                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> 1.  MySuperSales does buy platinum from people.  They purchase it from the same power guilds each time.  I have spoken to Jonathan Yantis about this and trust me, IGE/MSS buys plat everyday.<br /><br />2.  Inflation is caused by players not MSS/IGE.  Even before buying/selling plat the market was nuts.  Does IGE/MSS help the situation?  Absolutely not.  But to blame their company is ridiculous.  Their company does so well because players typically are greedy.  If it wasn't for the greedy players, the market for purchasing ingame assets wouldn't be so healthy.  I know MSS did about 170,000 different transactions last year so the market is obviously pretty good.<br /><br />3.  To think that Yantis and his team sit around daily and dupe plat is absurd.  You fail to realize that a lot of the UBER raiding guilds either a) sell the items to Yantis b) Sell the items for an inflated price in the bazaar then sell the plat to Yantis or c) work for Yantis.<br /><br />-------------------------<br /><br />Am I taking up for Yantis?  No.<br /><br />Is Yantis to blame for the economy in EQ?  No<br /><br />All Yantis has done is find a niche and use it to make a living.  That is how businesses are run.  Almost every game in existence has some sort of product line, additional programs, or business tied to it.  Even FPSs have expansion packs, level packs, written by people that have no ties to the original company.  They are companies designed to lease game servers, sell stats parsers, the list goes on.<br /><br />Business is business.  In any situation where there is a victor, you will have people that do the easiest route to get there.  So buying a character, plat, items, levels is the easy way.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
