                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Basically I think of it like this...<br /><br />If you really want to upgrade your gear, you have two options.<br /><br />1.  Attain the items yourself<br />2.  Buy them for what the seller deems a reasonable price<br /><br />I can promise you that if patterns weren't selling at 120k then no one would have them marked as such.  Hell think about how much people sell Funeral Pyre for.  Why do people charge such high prices, because they know the greed of the normal player will allow them to.  If you disagree with the outrageous prices on a particular item then don't purchase it.  It's a pretty easy solution.  I remember back in early / late beta, that gossamer robes were all the rage.  WHY?  Because it was the only white robe in the game.  It was a rare drop from trash in the ever dangerous befallen.  They sold for ridiculous amounts of money because players would pay for it.  <br /><br />The greed and the player's search to make their characters appear the sexiest/coolest is the root cause of the economy in EQ.  It has always been a part of the game and to feebly attempt to blame a 3rd party company is ludicrous.</span id="msg"></font></td>
